sec.p:
The primary aims of the study were to determine:
the dose limiting toxicity (DLT) and MTD of DaunoXome when given as a single infusion over 1 h to children with relapsed or resistant solid tumours in two cohorts, one having received conventional therapy and the other prior craniospinal radiotherapy or high-dose therapy;
a second DLT and MTD in each cohort of patients with G-CSF support using the MTD from the previous study;
the pharmacokinetics of liposomal daunorubicin in children.
